                android:layout_marginTop="30dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:gravity="center"
                android:text="Medu Vada is an easy-to-make South Indian recipe, which is a perfect amalgamation of southern spices and crispy vada served with Sambhar and coconut chutney.With festivals around the corner, this Medu Vada recipe makes for a delicious side dish. If you have sudden guests dropping by and you are not in mood to prepare something elaborate, then this makes for a delightful side dish and we bet your guests will love this delectable surprise. Traditionally, this Medu Vada was relished as a breakfast delight and a mid-time snack; However, if you want to enjoy this delectable dish as a main-course dish you can serve it with Sambhar and chutney. If you are fond of vadas and want to relish its flavour during summers, you can pair it with a bowl of yoghurt topped with finely chopped green chilies, onions and coriander; seasoned with a dash of salt powder and gunpowder. You can add your own twist of flavours to this quick recipe, however, the basic recipe will remain the same. You can just tweak some spices as per your taste preference and enjoy the delicious flavour of this authentic Indian recipe. Next time when you want to relish something delicious without putting in much efforts, then, try this crispy vada recipe and indulge in the flavoursome delight.  "
                android:textColor="@color/colorAccent" />
